                            <comment id="12907055" author="stuhood" created="Wed, 8 Sep 2010 01:52:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;From Peter Nerg on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-1474&quot; title=&quot;SimpleAuthenticator with MD5 does not work&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-1474&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-1474&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When running the SimpleAuthenticator in MD5 mode it will try to compare the plain text password with a MD5 digest from the passwd.properties file.&lt;br/&gt;
However the password in the property file is already a MD5 digest thus it&apos;s now digested twice.&lt;br/&gt;
Code snippet&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
case MD5:&lt;br/&gt;
authenticated = MessageDigest.isEqual(password.getBytes(), MessageDigest.getInstance(&quot;MD5&quot;).digest(props.getProperty(username).getBytes()));&lt;br/&gt;
break;&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12914894" author="jbellis" created="Sat, 25 Sep 2010 23:58:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12914966" author="hudson" created="Sun, 26 Sep 2010 12:47:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Cassandra #547 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra/547/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra/547/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    fix SimpleAuthenticator MD5 support&lt;br/&gt;
